extends ../layout/stories/story.jade
block append meta
    meta(property='og:url', content='http://julia.im/stories/bangkok')
    meta(property='og:type', content='website')
    meta(property='og:title', content='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.img + ' by Julia Khusainova')
    meta(property='og:image', content='http://julia.im/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/thumb_600.jpg')
    meta(property='og:description', content=stories.bangkok.description)

    link(rel='http://julia.im/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/thumb_600.jpg', type="image/jpeg", href='http://julia.im/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img)

block content

    section#main.story-page
        .featured-story#bangkok
        .featured-overlay

        .story-title
            .h-container
                .story-date June 2014
                h1 #{stories.bangkok.title}
                p.story-subtitle #{stories.bangkok.description}
    .h-container.content-container
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p.wiki Bangkok (English pronunciation: /ˈbæŋkɒk/) is the capital and the most populous city of Thailand. It is known in Thai as Krung Thep Maha Nakhon (กรุงเทพมหานคร). Bangkok traces its roots to a small trading post during the Ayutthaya Kingdom in the 15th century, which eventually grew in size and became the site of two capital cities: Thonburi in 1768 and Rattanakosin in 1782.
                
                    .column.half
                        .globe-span
                        p.icontitle Timezone: GMT+7
                    .column.half
                        .money-span
                        p.icontitle Currency: Baht

        //- First steps
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    h2 First steps in Bangkok
                    p Arrived. 17 hours flight with 2 hours layover was exsausting. Bangkok greeted me with humid, hot wheather and exotic, well, everything.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/1.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/e/bangkok@2x.png' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p First thing in the morning I went exploring the surrounding area and I had my first ever breakfast in local Thai cafe. Thai cuisine is relatively vegetarian friendly.
        .row
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/147.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/35.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p The streets in Bangkok are narrow, crowded and noisy. Huge greyish buildings, decorated with splash of colors and funny looking canopies. Fresh laundry, dried fruits, plants, old pots, wires - all these elements are part of Bangkok street view. They look in place and together create special vibe of the city.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/145.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p Bangkok is a city of contrast: traffic jams, polluted air, humid wheather.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/3.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/29.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/26.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/34.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p Steel buildings stand next to shiny temples, beautiful flowers dangling from the mirrors of old buses and tuk tuks.
        .row
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/17.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/36.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/33.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')

        //- Tuk tuk

        .row
            .column
                .text
                   p The tiny tuk-tuk is a vehicle of choice for Thai people and tourists. It's a hybrid of a motocycle, car and cabriolette.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/18.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/43.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')

        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p Not the safest choice you could go with but no doubt, the most entertaining one in the city (except for, maybe, elephants). Of course, we took a ride!
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/e/tuk@2x.png' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')

        .row
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/138.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/38.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')


        .row
            .column
                .text
                    h2 Khao San Road
                    p Relatively close to my place there is Khao San Road, I decided to walk through it to get a taste of local culture. Quite literally. The famous Thai street food is incredible and you'll find yourself wondering around not recognizing half of weird looking fruits and vegetables including smelly Durian (ทุเรียน) and Longan (ลำไย).
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/8.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p.point
                        span.fi-anchor
                        | Khao San Road
                        a(href='https://www.google.com/maps/place/Khaosan+Rd,+Khet+Phra+Nakhon,+Krung+Thep+Maha+Nakhon+10200,+Thailand/@13.7589615,100.4971845,17z/data=!4m7!1m4!3m3!1s0x30e29912cab71d0d:0x40b71c7b0079a776!2sKhaosan+Rd,+Khet+Phra+Nakhon,+Krung+Thep+Maha+Nakhon+10200,+Thailand!3b1!3m1!1s0x30e29912cab71d0d:0x40b71c7b0079a776' target='_blank') View on map
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/9.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p Chang is the most popular beer in Thailand. It's everywhere - every bar, breakfast place or restuarant offers it. The multitude of shops, Tattoo studios and divercity of tourist population completes the picture of Khao San Road.
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    h2 Grand Palace
                    p One of the must visit places in Bangkok is Grand Palace. For more than 150 years it was the home of the Thai King, the Royal court and the administrative seat of government.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/16.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/12.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/15.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p.point
                        span.fi-anchor
                        | Grand Palace
                        a(href='https://www.google.com/maps/dir//Grand+Palace,+Na+Phra+Lan+Rd,+Phra+Nakhon,+Bangkok,+10200/@13.7527219,100.4911017,17z/data=!4m12!1m3!3m2!1s0x0000000000000000:0xc7c8e2e28e73a435!2sGrand+Palace!4m7!1m0!1m5!1m1!1s0x30e2990f1400adc9:0xc7c8e2e28e73a435!2m2!1d100.491535!2d13.750335' target='_blank') View on map
        .row
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/49.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/45.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p Royal Reception Hall is impressive with its architecture, style and details.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/48.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/114.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/119.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')

        .row
            .column
                .text
                    h2 Wat Pra Kaew (Temple of Emerald Buddha)
                    p Wat Phra Kaew is a part of the Grand Palace. It contains the famous Emerald Buddha that dates back to the 14th century.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/52.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/86.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p.point
                        span.fi-anchor
                        | Wat Pra Kaew
                        a(href='https://www.google.com/maps/place/wat+phra+kaew/@13.751426,100.492573,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xe1cce47d89865836?sa=X&ei=CFU-Vd34JJCYoQSu4YCQAQ&ved=0CJABEPwSMA8' target='_blank') View on map
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p The main building is the central hall, where the Emerald Buddha resides - the most important icon for Thai people.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/63.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p Phra Kaew includes a model of Angkor Wat, which was built under the order of King Rama IV when Cambodia was under Siamese control. The model was later recreated in plaster at the behest of King Rama V to celebrate the first centenary of the Royal City.
        .row
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/65.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/66.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p The entrance is guarded by a pair of yakshis.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/59.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/125.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')      
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/127.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')      
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/113.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')      
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p The Emerald Buddha deified in the Wat Phra Kaew is deeply revered and venerated in Thailand as the protector of the country.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/128.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')      
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/131.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')      
                .credit
                    span Photo credit: Dylan Pyle
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p By the way, the legendary history of this Buddha image is traced to India, five centuries after Gautama Buddha attained Nirvana, until it was finally enshrined in Bangkok at the Wat Phra Kaew temple in 1782.
        .row
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/133.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')      
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/84.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')      
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p Wat Phra Kaew (Thai: วัดพระแก้ว, English: Temple of the Emerald Buddha; full official name Wat Phra Si Rattana Satsadaram, Thai: วัดพระศรีรัตนศาสดาราม, is regarded the most sacred Buddhist temple in Thailand.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/132.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')      
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    h2 Wat Pho (Temple of the Reclining Buddha)
                    p Wat Pho (Thai: วัดโพธิ์) is one of the oldest temples in Bangkok. The image of Reclining Buddha is gigantic - 15m high and 43m long with his right arm supporting the head with tight curls on two box-pillows.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/116.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/117.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/118.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p.point
                        span.fi-anchor
                        | Wat Pho
                        a(href='https://www.google.com/maps/place/Wat+Pho/@13.746575,100.492728,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x7df49a08f511c22e' target='_blank') View on map
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    h2 Chakri Maha Prasat
                    p The Phra Thinang Chakri Maha Prasat (พระที่นั่งจักรีมหาปราสาท) is located on what used to be a garden. It's a throne hall for Thai kings.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/91.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')      
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p Phra Thinang Chakri Maha Prasat is a blend of Thai traditional architecture and a combination of 19th-century European styles.
        .row
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/101.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/97.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')  

        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/100.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')      
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p Carefully cut grass, round shaped trees, sculptures and vases, modern decorations - all these are signs of European influence on Thai culture reflected in a way we see Grand Palace.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/104.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')      
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p Can easily imaging Thai Kings walking within these walls in the sunny humid afternoon thinking about the future of Thai people.
        .row
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/105.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')      
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/106.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')      
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/115.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')      
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    h2 MOCA (Museum of Contemporary Art)
                    p Museum of Contemporary Art (MOCA) in Bangkok is a place to visit if you want to get yourself familiar with Thai history and art. Thai people are extremely talented when it comes to art - you can see that nowadays from beautifully decorated temples to fancy looking restuarants and cafes. 
        .row
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/148.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/149.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/150.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
                .credit
                        span Photo credit: Dylan Pyle
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    h2 Night Bangkok
                    p Magnificent view of tropical trees over the chanel reminds of autumn in Southern Europe.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/137.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p One night in Bangkok, right? Bangkok shines a thousand lights at night. Bars, dance clubs, cars lights, billboards - all this mixed up, shaked and served in strong coconut cocktail.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/143.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
                .credit
                    span Photo credit: Dylan Pyle
        .row
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/141.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
            .column.half
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/142.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
        .row
            .column
                .text
                    p "Bangkok, like Las Vegas, sounds like a place where you make bad decisions" - Todd Phillips, Director.
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/e/flag.png' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
         .row
            .column
                .text
                    p Post scriptum: I fell in love with exotic south east asian culture. I'm coming back...
        .row
            .column
                img.lazy(src='/images/i.png' data-src='/images/stories/' + stories.bangkok.img + '/42.jpg' alt='Story about ' + stories.bangkok.title + ' by Julia Khusainova')
